                                    </label>
                                </div>
                                <h5 class="teachingmd-hd">Simulated learning</h5>
                                <p>
                                    Simulated learning uses a ‘hands’ on approach to teaching using real life
                                    environments/contexts, whilst the lecturer maintains the safety, integrity and
                                    wellbeing of all involved. Simulated learning is designed to enhance student
                                    understanding by engaging them in solving complex interdependent situations. The
                                    process requires learners to integrate theory and practice, apply skills learned
                                    and then, under the direction of their lecturer, reflect on the process/practice.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4 col-sm-4">
                            <div class="panel teaching-methods">
                                <div class="normal-checkbox">
                                    <label class="checkbox checkbox--material">
                                        <input autocomplete="nope" type="checkbox" class="checkbox__input checkbox--material__input">
